trans-unit.source: Encapsulates a collection of <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> objects that represent a single row in a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.Table"></xref> control.
This class cannot be inherited.
Use this class to programmatically manage a collection of <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow> objects.
This class is commonly used to add or remove rows from a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Table> control.

A <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Table> control contains a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Table.Rows%2A> collection that represents a collection of <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow> objects.

Each <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow> represents an individual row in the table and contains a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow.Cells%2A> collection that represents a collection of <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableCell> objects.
These <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableCell> objects represent the individual cells in the table.

To get an individual cell, you must first get a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow> from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Table.Rows%2A> collection of a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Table> control.
You can then get a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableCell> from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow.Cells%2A> collection of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow>.
Appends the specified <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> object to the end of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref>.
Use this method to add a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow> object to the end of a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection>.
The <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> object to add to the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref>.
The index of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref>.
Adds the specified <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> object to the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref> at the specified index location.
Use this method to insert the specified <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow> in a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection> at the specified index.
The location in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref> at which to add the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> object to add to the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref>.
Appends the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> objects from the specified array to the end of the collection.
Use the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection.AddRange%2A> method to append the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow> objects from the specified array to the collection.
This method is commonly used when you are constructing a table.
To construct a table, first create an array of <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow> objects to represent the rows of the table.
Next, use the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection.AddRange%2A> method, passing the array as an argument, to add the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow> objects to the collection.
The array containing the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> objects to add to the collection.
The value of the rows parameter is `null`.
Removes all <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> controls from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref>.

Use this method to remove all <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow> objects from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection> and set the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection.Count%2A> property to 0.

Copies the items from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref> to the specified <xref href="System.Array"></xref>, starting with the specified index in the <xref href="System.Array"></xref>.
Use this method to copy the contents of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection> into the specified <xref:System.Array?displayProperty=fullName>, starting at the specified index.
The `array` parameter must be a zero-based <xref:System.Array?displayProperty=fullName>.
A zero-based <xref href="System.Array"></xref> that receives the copied items from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref>.
The first position in the specified <xref href="System.Array"></xref> to receive copied contents.
Gets the number of <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> objects in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref>.
Use this property to determine the number of rows in the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection>.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection.Count%2A> property is often used when iterating through the collection to determine the upper bound.
The number of <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> objects in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref>.
The default is 0.

Returns a <xref href="System.Collections.IEnumerator"></xref> implemented object that contains all <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> objects within the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref>.

Use this method to create a <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator?displayProperty=fullName> implemented object that can be iterated through easily to get each item in the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection>.
Use the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property to get the item currently pointed to in the collection.
Use the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method to move to the next item in the collection.
Use the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method to move the enumerator back to the initial position.

The <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method must be called after creating a <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator?displayProperty=fullName> implemented object or using the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method to move the enumerator to the first item in the collection.
Otherwise, the item represented by the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property is undefined.

A <xref href="System.Collections.IEnumerator"></xref> implemented object that contains all <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> objects within the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref>.
Returns a value that represents the index of the specified <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref>.
Use this method to determine the index of the specified <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow> in the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection>.
If the specified <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow> is not found, an index of -1 is returned.
The <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> object to search for in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref>.
The ordinal index position of the specified <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> within the collection.
The default is -1, which indicates that the specified <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> has not been found.
Gets a value indicating whether the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref> is read-only.
This property always returns `false` to indicate that the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection> can be written to in all cases.
`false` for all cases.
Gets a value indicating whether access to the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref> is synchronized (thread-safe).
This property is derived from <xref:System.Collections.ICollection?displayProperty=fullName> and is overridden to always return `false`.

For more information on the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableCellCollection.IsSynchronized%2A> property, see the <xref:System.Collections.ICollection.IsSynchronized%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property of the <xref:System.Collections.ICollection?displayProperty=fullName> interface.
`false` for all cases.
Gets a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref> at the specified index.
Use this indexer to get an individual <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow> from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection> at the specified index using simple array notation.
An ordinal index value that specifies which <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> object to return.
This index is zero-based.
A <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> that represents an element in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref>.
Removes the specified <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref>.
Use this method to remove the specified <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow> from a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection>.
The <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> object to remove from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref>.
Removes a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref> at the specified index.
Use this method to remove a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow> from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection> at the specified index.
The index of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRow"></xref> object to remove from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref>.
Gets the object that can be used to synchronize access to the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection"></xref>.
The object returned in this implementation is the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection> itself.

For more information on the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableCellCollection.SyncRoot%2A> property, see the <xref:System.Collections.ICollection.SyncRoot%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property of the <xref:System.Collections.ICollection?displayProperty=fullName> interface.
An object that can be used to synchronize access to the collection.
Adds an object to the collection.

Typically, you should use the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection.Add%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method to add an element to a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection> object.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection.System%23Collections%23IList%23Add%2A> method is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.IList> interface.
The object to add to the collection.
The index at which the object was added to the collection.
Determines whether the specified object is contained within the collection.

The object to locate within the collection.
`true` if the object is in the collection; otherwise, `false`.
Searches for the specified object and returns the zero-based index of the first occurrence within the collection.

The object to locate within the collection.
The zero-based index of the first occurrence of the object within the collection; otherwise, -1 if the object is not in the collection.
Inserts an object into the collection at the specified index.

It can be used only when the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableRowCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.IList> interface.
The zero-based index within the collection at which to insert the object.
The object to insert into the collection.
For a description of this member, see <xref href="System.Collections.IList.IsFixedSize"></xref>.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.

`true` if the list has a fixed size; otherwise, `false`
